NEW DELHI, India, January 5, 2017/APO/ --
                                                
                        President of Rwanda His Excellency Paul Kagame will be on a working visit to India from 9-12 January 2017 on an invitation extended by Prime Minister Narendra Modi. The two leaders will hold official talks on 09 January 2017 in Gandhinagar. A business delegation would accompany the President Kagame.
Â 

President Kagame will attend the Vibrant Gujarat Global Summit scheduled to be held at Gandhinagar and will be addressing a National Business Seminar on Rwanda. Rwanda will also be participating in the Global Trade Show 2017.